2%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Grammy%20Awards%20Have%20a%20Category%20for%20Africa%20Now%20%E2%80%93%20But%20What%20Does%20This%20Mean%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04114007%2FUntitled-design-7.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20its%2065-year%20history%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammy.com%5C%22%3EGrammy%20Awards%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20has%20introduced%20an%20African%20category%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammy.com%2Fnews%2Fbest-african-music-performance-category-2024-grammys-roundtable%5C%22%3EBest%20African%20Music%20Performance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20recognises%20the%20song%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Grammys%20is%20the%20most%20prestigious%20award%20in%20the%20largest%20music%20industry%20in%20the%20world.%20Its%20focus%20has%20always%20been%20US%20music%20styles%20in%20categories%20like%20pop%2C%20R%26amp%3BB%2C%20rap%2C%20country%2C%20jazz%20and%20classical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20musical%20styles%20from%20abroad%20(or%20in%20Spanish)%20have%20moved%20into%20the%20US%20commercial%20market%2C%20the%20Grammy%20Foundation%20has%20tried%20to%20recognise%20them%20%E2%80%93%20beyond%20the%20generic%20%E2%80%9Cfolk%20music%E2%80%9D%20category%20it%20first%20used%20to%20put%20them%20in.%20So%20categories%20were%20established%20like%20Latin%2C%20Mexican%2C%20reggae%2C%20world%20music%20and%20global%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20Africa%20has%20its%20own%20best%20song%20category%2C%20the%20first%20continent%20with%20this%20distinction.%20This%20is%20clearly%20a%20nod%20to%20the%20growing%20popularity%20of%20African%20music%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20notably%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Ffrom-nigeria-to-the-world-afrobeats-is-having-a-global-moment-179910%5C%22%3EAfrobeats%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Nigeria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFew%20African%20artists%20received%20Grammy%20nominations%20until%201992%2C%20when%20the%20Best%20World%20Music%20Album%20category%20was%20added.%20A%20diverse%20range%20of%20African%20music%20came%20to%20dominate%20this%20category.%20But%20%E2%80%9Cworld%20music%E2%80%9D%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fmusic%2F2019%2Fjul%2F24%2Fguardian-world-music-outdated-global%5C%22%3Ecriticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20being%20outmoded.%20The%20award%20was%20renamed%20Best%20Global%20Music%20Album%20in%202021.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammy.com%2Fnews%2Fwhy-grammy-awards-best-global-music-album-category-name-change-matters%5C%22%3Ereasons%20given%3C%2Fa%3E%20included%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20symbolises%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20connotations%20of%20colonialism%2C%20folk%20and%20%E2%80%98non-American%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20name%20came%20with%20a%20shift%20in%20which%20music%20received%20nominations.%20%E2%80%9CWorld%20music%E2%80%9D%20tended%20to%20recognise%20regional%20music%20styles%20released%20on%20small%20independent%20labels.%20%E2%80%9CGlobal%20music%E2%80%9D%20was%20seemingly%20more%20focused%20on%20more%20commercial%20music%20that%20was%20also%20reaching%20the%20US%20charts.%20It%20tended%20to%20reward%20Afrobeats%20and%20other%20popular%20electronic%20dance%20music%20that%20took%20creative%20cues%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20music%20represents%20and%20expresses%20identity%20and%20cultural%20authenticity%20has%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2Fj.ctt16gz8kj%5C%22%3Ekey%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DB6-wCjIAAAAJ%26hl%3Den%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20ethnomusicologist.%20Certainly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DYddCALG4qJE%26t%3D3011s%5C%22%3Egenerational%20shifts%3C%2Fa%3E%20happen%20and%20interests%20in%20some%20deeply%20rooted%20traditions%20may%20fade%20in%20favour%20of%20new%20global%20currents.%20But%20still%2C%20I%20have%20mixed%20reactions%20to%20the%20new%20award.%20The%20economic%20boon%20that%20the%20Grammys%20brings%20to%20the%20African%20music%20industry%20could%20be%20significant.%20But%20at%20what%20cost%20to%20its%20diversity%20of%20offerings%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Grammys%20claims%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.recordingacademy.com%2Fabout%5C%22%3Erecognise%20excellence%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20also%20celebrates%20US%20cultural%20imperialism%20and%20commercial%20success%20%E2%80%93%20a%20track%20record%20evident%20in%20its%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20first%20batch%20of%20best%20performance%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammy.com%2Fnews%2F2024-grammys-nominees-best-african-music-performance%5C%22%3Enominees%3C%2Fa%3E%20provides%20further%20clues%20that%20US%20record%20conglomerates%20are%20strongly%20shaping%20Grammy%20recognition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EAfrica%20at%20the%20Grammys%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20Grammy%20Awards%20ceremony%20was%20in%201959%2C%20the%20same%20year%20South%20African%20star%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-legacy-of-iconic-singer-miriam-makeba-and-her-art-of-activism-178230%5C%22%3EMiriam%20Makeba%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20toured%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201960%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammy.com%2Fawards%2F2nd-annual-grammy-awards%5C%22%3EBest%20Folk%20Performance%3C%2Fa%3E%20category%20was%20added.%20This%20was%20the%20key.%20In%201961%20Makeba%20received%20three%20nominations%20(new%20artist%2C%20female%20vocalist%20and%20folk).%20She%20was%20the%20first%20African%20artist%20nominated%20and%20it%20happened%20again%20in%201964%20and%201965.%20Folk%20was%20the%20only%20category%20that%20could%20accommodate%20singing%20like%20hers%20%E2%80%93%20in%20South