e%20past%20five%20years%20he%20has%20launched%20a%20succession%20of%20unbridled%20personal%20attacks%20on%20the%20leaders%20of%20all%20rival%20political%20parties%2C%20tamed%20the%20judiciary%2C%20harnessed%20the%20central%20investigative%20agencies%2C%20virtually%20wiped%20out%20habeas%20corpus%20and%20destroyed%20civil%20liberties%2C%20most%20notably%20the%20right%20of%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20Destruction%20of%20Dissent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20headed%20the%20governments%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20India%20for%2022%20years%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20thirst%20for%20absolute%20power%20has%20remained%20unquenched.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20a%20safe%20bet%20to%20say%20that%20if%20and%20when%20he%20comes%20back%20to%20power%2C%20every%20remaining%20voice%20that%20seeks%20to%20safeguard%20civil%20liberties%20and%20uphold%20the%20right%20to%20dissent%20will%20be%20silenced%2C%20and%20every%20constitutional%20institution%20designed%20to%20safeguard%20these%20will%20be%20robbed%20of%20its%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20his%20desertion%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20Nitish%20Kumar%20has%20immeasurably%20increased%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20chances%20of%20success.%20Future%20historians%20will%20remember%20him%20as%20the%20Benedict%20Arnold%2C%20or%20the%20Mir%20Jafar%20of%20democratic%20India.%20But%20the%20question%20that%20will%20remain%20to%20haunt%20them%20is%20that%20when%20Nitish%20Kumar%20was%20the%20first%20chief%20minister%20to%20advocate%20the%20formation%20of%20an%20anti-BJP%20alliance%20as%20long%20back%20as%20in%202016%2C%20and%20even%20stayed%20away%20from%20Modi%20in%202014%2C%20why%20was%20he%20the%20first%20person%20to%20stab%20it%20in%20the%20back%20after%20it%20was%20finally%20formed%3F%20The%20facile%20answer%2C%20now%20given%20by%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20others%20in%20the%20Congress%2C%20is%20that%20he%20is%20an%20unprincipled%20politician%20who%20is%20determined%20to%20stay%20on%20the%20winning%20side%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20it%20costs%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20have%20been%20credible%20on%20January%2030%2C%20when%20Gandhi%20said%20it.%20But%20five%20days%20later%2C%20when%20both%20the%20Trinamul%20Congress%20in%20Bengal%20and%20the%20(much%20smaller%20and%20less%20influential)%20Tamil%20Maanila%20Congress%20(TMC)%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20have%20also%20questioned%20the%20utility%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20find%20another%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeeded%20for%20INDIA%3A%20A%20Principle%20for%20Allocation%20of%20Seats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20essential%20step%20towards%20creating%20a%20viable%20alternative%20to%20the%20BJP%20for%20the%202024%20election%20would%20have%20been%20to%20announce%20a%20principle%20for%20the%20allocation%20of%20seats%20within%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20that%20was%20palpably%20fair.%20One%20was%20there%2C%20staring%20the%20leaders%20in%20the%20face%2C%20since%20the%20first%20day%20when%20the%20Alliance%20was%20mooted.%20This%20was%20to%20leave%20the%20242%20seats%20that%20the%20BJP%20did%20not%20win%20in%202019%20untouched%20and%20allot%20the%20303%20seats%20it%20had%20won%20to%20the%20first%20runner%20up.%20This%20might%20have%20left%20a%20handful%20of%20seats%20where%20changes%20that%20had%20occurred%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%20could%20have%20justified%20a%20different%20allocation.%20But%20these%20would%20have%20been%20easy%20to%20manage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20requirement%20was%20the%20framing%20of%20a%20common%20campaign%20agenda.%20This%20required%20highlighting%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20failure%20meet%20its%20grandiose%20economic%20promises%20during%20its%20first%20term%20in%20office%2C%20and%20its%20ruthless%20assault%20on%20peoples%E2%80%99%20rights%20and%20freedoms%20during%20its%20second.%20From%20the%20steady%20decline%20of%20the%20economy%E2%80%99s%20growth%20rate%2C%20the%20pain%20caused%20by%20a%20blundering%20and%20unnecessary%20demonetisation%2C%20sharp%20and%20continuing%20rise%20in%20unemployment%2C%20the%20encouragement%20of%20communal%20attacks%20on%20the%20minorities%20and%20the%20perversion%20of%20the%20judicial%20system%20to%20ensure%20that%20none%20of%20the%20attackers%20got%20punished%2C%20As%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20the%20Alliance%2C%20and%20the%20one%20with%20the%20greatest%20experience%20of%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20the%20Congress%20needed%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20in%20preparing%20this%20offensive.%20Apart%20from%20occasional%20walkouts%20in%20parliament%20it%20did%20no%20such%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20such%20a%20concerted%20counter-attack%20on%20the%20BJP%20government%20would%20have%20taken%20some%20time%2C%20but%20the%20most%20immediate%20and%20effective%20way%20of%20cementing%20the%20alliance%20would%20have%20been%20to%20rise%20to%20the%20defence%20of%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20whom%20Modi%20was%20systematically%20singling%20out%20for%20attack%2C%20humiliation%20and%20arbitrary%20imprisonment%20under%20its%20own%20authoritarian%20amendments%20to%20the%20criminal%20and%20economic%20offence%20laws.%20Tragically%2C%20it%20did%20no%20such%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20not%20only%20did%20it%20maintain%20a%20Sphinx-like%20silence%20throughout%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20on%20members%20of%20the%20Alliance.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%E2%80%99s%20supposed%20%E2%80%98liquor%20scam%E2%80%99%20in%20Delhi%2C%20its%20local%20leaders%20openly%20praised%20the%20Modi%20government%20for%20putting%20Satyender%20Jain%20and%20Manish%20Sisodia%20in%20gaol%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20told%20you%20they%20were%20corrupt%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F03120811%2FFnoRwCpakAAif8S.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F03120811%2FFnoRwCpakAAif8S.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F03120811%2FFnoRwCpakAAif8S-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F03120811%2FFnoRwCpakAAif8S-1024x684.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-638894%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%20in%20Kashmir.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40bharatjodo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECongress%20must%20introspect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20short-sighted%20follies%20does%20not%20end%20there.%20The%20crowning%20one%20has%20been%20the%20timing%20of%20its%20launch%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyaya%20Yatra.%20Had%20the%20party%20done%20this%20after%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20had%20agreed%20on%20the%20principles%20it%20would%20adopt%20to%20choose%20its%20candidates%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20neither%20Mamta%20nor%20Nitish%20would%20have%20felt%20threatened%20by%20it.%20But%20by%20embarking%20upon%20it%20when%20none%20of%20these%20issues%20had%20been%20resolved%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20has%20ensured%20that%20every%20additional%20vote%20the%20Congress%20succeeds%20in%20capturing%20will%20be%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20in%20Bengal%2C%20and%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20believing%20that%20this%20will%20happen%20is%20to%20be%20found%20in%20the%20shift%20in%20voting%20pattern%20that%20took%20place%20in%20the%20Karnataka%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20election%20last%20May%20after%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Bharat%20Jodo%20yatra%20had%20passed%20through%20the%20state.%20In%20it%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20vote%20hardly%20budged.%20Almost%20all%20of%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20increase%20in%20votes%20came%20from%20Deve%20Gowda%E2%80%99s%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20or%20JD(S).%20This%20shift%20ousted%20the%20BJP%20because%20the%20Congress%20was%20the%20only%20opposition%20party%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20had%20a%20strong%20cadre%20base%20and%20therefore%20had%20a%20good%20chance%20of%20winning.%20In%20sharp%20contrast%2C%20the%20Congress%20is%20a%20minor%20player%20in%20all%20of%20the%20states%20that%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Nyaya%20Yatra%20is%20going%20through%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20Chhattisgarh.%20Any%20shift%20of%20vote%20to%20the%20Congress%20because%20of%20the%20Nyaya%20Yatra%20will%20therefore%20only%20weaken%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20main%20opponent.%20The%20Congress%20has%20every%20right%20to%20strengthen%20itself%20but%20not%20when%20the%20immediate%20logic%20of%20the%20INDIA%20coalition%20demands%20the%20defeat%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20as%20many%20seats%20as%20possible%20rather%20than%20the%20maximisation%20of%20individual%20party%20tallies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20little%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Yatra%20will%20matter%20to%20the%20BJP%20can%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20in%202019%20it%20won%2014%20of%20its%2018%20seats%20in%20Bengal%20with%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20vote.%20In%20those%20constituencies%20the%20BJP%20will%20remain%2C%20impregnable.%20Rahul%E2%80%99s%20second%20yatra%20might%20increase%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20vote%20in%20Bengal%20by%20two%20to%20three%20percentage%20points%2C%20but%20what%20difference%20will%20that%20make%20to%20the%20Alliance%3F%20For%20in%202019%20the%20Congress%20won%20only%20one%20seat%20out%20of%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%2042%2C%20and%20was%20the%20runner%20up%20in%20only%20one%20more%2C%20Murshidabad.%20Even%20there%20the%20margin%20of%20its%20loss%20was%2020.1%25.%20This%20is%20a%20gap%20that%20no%20form%20of%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%20can%20bridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20entering%20Bengal%20is%20going%20to%20be%20counterproductive%2C%20carrying%20on%20to%20Bihar%20will%20be%20suicidal.%20For%20in%20Bihar%20too%20the%20Congress%20won%20only%20one%20seat%20in%202019%2C%20and%20was%20the%20runner%20up%20in%20only%206%20more%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%2040%20constituencies.%20What%20is%20more%2C%20the%20margins%20with%20which%20it%20lost%20in%20these%20seats%20ranged%20from%2057%2C000%20to%203%2C54%2C000%20votes.%20No%20Yatra%20can%20bridge%20such%20a%20huge%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20Kumar%20was%20fully%20aware%20of%20not%20only%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20weakness%2C%20but%20also%20its%20overweening%2C%20and%20entirely%20unrealistic%20ambitions%2C%20which%20would%20almost%20certainly%20have%20made%20it%20ask%20for%20a%20disproportionately%20high%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20Bihar.%20He%20has%20therefore%20decided%20to%20cut%20his%20losses%20and%20rejoin%20what%20he%20is%20now%20convinced%20will%20be%20the%20winning%20side%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20this%20year.%20Since%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20rivals%20are%20all%20members%20of%20the%20Alliance%2C%20the%20Nyaya%20Yatra%20is%20likely%20to%20work%20against%20them%20in%20all%20but%20one%20or%20two%20of%20the%2015%20states%20he%20will%20traverse.%20In%20the%20rest%2C%20the%20net%20beneficiary%20will%20be%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrem%20Shankar%20Jha%20is%20a%20veteran%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707025721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04111627%2FUntitled-design-6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fopposition-needs-a-roadmap-for-the-2024-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Developing%20a%20concerted%20counter-attack%20on%20the%20BJP%20government%20would%20have%20been%20to%20rise%20to%20the%20defence%20of%20opposition%20leaders%20who%20Modi%20was%20targeting.%22%2C%22author%22