png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuwahati%2FNew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20a%20response%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fassam-himanta-biswa-sarma-public-money-helicopter-chartered-flights-bjp-party-wedding%5C%22%3Ethe%20report%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3EThe%20CrossCurrent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20right%20to%20information%20(RTI)%20reply%20by%20the%20Assam%20government%2C%20which%20illustrates%20how%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20chief%20minister%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20may%20have%20used%20public%20money%20to%20attend%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%E2%80%99s%20meetings%20and%20some%20social%20engagements%20besides%20campaigning%20for%20a%20party%20ally%20in%20an%20election%2C%20the%20Assam%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20(CMO)%20termed%20it%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCMOfficeAssam%2Fstatus%2F1753662808846401929%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cmischievous%2C%20misleading%20and%20lazy%20hit%20job%20based%20on%20selective%20reading%20of%20handful%20of%20tweets%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20close%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20bills%20obtained%20through%20the%20RTI%20and%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20forbidding%20combining%20elections%20with%20official%20work%20do%20not%20bear%20this%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20response%2C%20the%20CMO%20has%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20expenditure%20of%20HCM%20Dr%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20election%20campaigns%20are%20borne%20by%20the%20State%20exchequer.%20All%20expenses%2C%20including%20flights%2C%20are%20paid%20for%20by%20the%20political%20party%20via%20bank%20transfer%2Fcheque.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CMO%20claims%20that%20whenever%20he%20%E2%80%9Cvisits%20any%20district%20in%20the%20State%20or%20neighbouring%20States%20for%20official%20engagements%2C%20there%20could%20be%20social%20functions%20such%20as%20condolence%20meetings%20or%20weddings%20that%20coincide%20with%20the%20visit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CMO%20asserts%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccompared%20to%20all%20official%20visits%20undertaken%20by%20HCM%20since%20May%202021%2C%20such%20coincidences%20are%20far%20and%20few.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Though%20the%20CMO%20claims%20that%20%E2%80%9Call%20expenses%2C%20including%20flights%2C%20are%20paid%20for%20by%20the%20political%20party%20%5Bthe%20BJP%5D%20via%20bank%20transfer%2Fcheque%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20offer%20the%20details%20of%20such%20%E2%80%98cheque%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98bank%20transfers%E2%80%99%20pertaining%20to%20those%20dates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20the%20RTI%20replies%20nowhere%20stated%20that%20any%20payment%20or%20even%20a%20part%20of%20it%20was%20to%20be%20borne%20by%20Sarma%E2%80%99s%20party%2C%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20Assam%20Tourism%20Development%20Corporation%20(ATDC)%2C%20through%20which%20an%20order%20to%20charter%20a%20special%20flight%20is%20placed%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20had%20placed%20a%20bill%20of%20Rs%201%2C26%2C56%2C267%20spent%20on%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20special%20flights%20to%20the%20general%20administration%20department%20on%20December%2024%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%2C%20numbered%201%2F32%2C%20was%20for%20his%20travel%20between%20October%201%20and%2019%2C%202023.%20The%20name%20of%20the%20service%20provider%20was%20Dhillon%20Aviation%20Private%20Limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20bill%20attached%20with%20the%20RTI%20replies%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20flew%20to%20Tamulpur%20on%20October%2017%2C%202023%20and%20to%20Gossaigaon%20on%20October%2018-19%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2017%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20took%20part%20in%20the%20election%20campaign%20for%20a%20candidate%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20ally%2C%20the%20United%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20Liberal%20(UPPL)%20in%20Tamulpur%20for%20the%20assembly%20by-election.%20On%20October%2019%2C%20he%20campaigned%20for%20another%20UPPL%20candidate%20contesting%20from%20Gossaigaon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20evidence%20was%20cited%20by%20the%20state%20government%20in%20the%20RTI%20replies%20about%20Sarma%E2%80%99s%20party%20bearing%20the%20cost%20of%20his%20air%20travel%20on%20those%20dates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20instance%20was%20the%20submission%20of%20a%20bill%20on%20April%202%2C%202022%20by%20the%20ATDC%20to%20the%20general%20administration%20department%20for%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs%201%2C40%2C92%2C109.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20that%20bill%2C%20numbered%201%2F58%2C%20the%20amount%20was%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20air%20travel%20by%20chartered%20flights%20between%20February%203%2C%202022%20and%20February%2028%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20showed%20that%20Sarma%20flew%20to%20Majuli%20on%20February%2016%2C%202022%2C%20where%20he%20participated%20in%20the%20nomination%20paper-submission%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20candidate%2C%20Bhuban%20Gam%2C%20who%20was%20contesting%20the%20by-election%20for%20the%20state%20assembly%20held%20after%20the%20seat%20fell%20vacant%20once%20former%20chief%20minister%20Sarbananda%20Sonowal%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20no%20evidence%20(of%20a%20cheque%20or%20by%20bank%20transfer)%20of%20the%20party%20picking%20up%20the%20tab%20was%20evident%20from%20the%20bill%20submitted%20by%20one%20government%20depart%20to%20the%20other%20to%20clear%20payments%20to%20the%20service%20provider.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20code%20of%20conduct%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20cannot%20mix%20election%20work%20with%20official%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fmcc%2F%5C%22%3EVII%201(a)%20of%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%20reads%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Ministers%20shall%20not%20combine%20their%20official%20visit%20with%20electioneering%20work%20and%20shall%20not%20also%20make%20use%20of%20official%20machinery%20or%20personnel%20during%20the%20electioneering%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20another%20bill%20submitted%20by%20the%20ATDC%20on%20February%2018%2C%202023%20(bill%20no%3A1%2F117)%2C%20a%20special%20flight%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%20from%20Mumbai%20to%20Delhi%20was%20hired%20on%20November%2020%2C%202022%2C%20then%20from%20Delhi%20to%20Guwahati%20the%20next%20day%20and%20then%20from%20Guwahati%20to%20Delhi%20on%20November%2022%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20cost%20the%20state%20exchequer%20Rs%2045%2C48%2C450.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2020%2C%202022%2C%20the%20day%20the%20chief%20minister%20travelled%20from%20Mumbai%20to%20Delhi%2C%20he%20was%20seen%20taking%20part%20in%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20for%20the%20Delhi%20municipal%20polls.%20The%20service%20provider%20for%20the%20entire%20three-day%20trip%20was%20Air%20King%20Chartered%20Private%20Limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%201%2C%202023%2C%20as%20per%20bill%20no.%201%2F141%20of%20the%20ATDC%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20flew%20from%20Agartala%20to%20Dibrugarh%20on%20January%2030%2C%202023%20and%20from%20there%20to%20Lucknow%20and%20back%20to%20Guwahati%20the%20next%20day.%20It%20had%20cost%20the%20government%20Rs%2040%2C53%2C580.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2030%2C%20he%20was%20present%20with%20Tripura%20chief%20minister%20Manik%20Saha%20while%20he%20filed%20his%20nomination%20papers%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections%20for%20that%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20bills%20were%20submitted%20by%20the%20ATDC%20to%20the%20general%20administration%20department%20for%20clearance%20of%20payment.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20of%20Sarma%E2%80%99s%20party%20paying%20for%20such%20non-official%20work%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20could%20well%20be%20social%20functions%20like%20condolence%20meetings%20and%20weddings%20%E2%80%98coinciding%E2%80%99%20with%20the%20official%20visit%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%20to%20a%20district%2C%20as%20claimed%20by%20the%20CMO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20unlike%20in%20a%20road%20journey%2C%20where%20the%20state%20typically%20needs%20to%20spend%20much%20less%20public%20money%20(in%20fuel%2C%20etc.)%20if%20the%20dignitary%20takes%20a%20detour%20from%20the%20official%20route%2C%20with%20flights%20and%20helicopters%2C%20the%20amount%20from%20extra%20time%20spent%20jumps%20up%20to%20the%20lakhs%20as%20it%20is%20billed%20on%20an%20hourly%20basis%2C%20as%20highlighted%20in%20our%20news%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20needs%20highlighting%20here%20is%20also%20this%3A%20as%20per%20a%20bill%20(no.%201%2F119)%20submitted%20by%20the%20ATDC%20on%20February%2017%2C%202023%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20flew%20by%20a%20special%20flight%20from%20Guwahati%20to%20Dimapur%20and%20back%20on%20November%2011%2C%202022%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%2014%2C08%2C562.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarma%E2%80%99s%20itinerary%2C%20seen%20in%20the%20RTI%20reply%2C%20showed%20that%20he%20went%20by%20road%20to%20the%20Guwahati%20airport%20on%20November%2011%2C%202022%20at%209%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2010%20am%2C%20he%20flew%20from%20Guwahati%20and%20landed%20in%20Dimapur%20at%2010%3A35%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2010%3A40%20am%2C%20he%20went%20by%20road%20straight%20to%20Rio%20Villa%20at%20Suvima%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2010%3A50%20am.%2C%20he%20attended%20Nagaland%20chief%20minister%20Neiphiu%20Rio%E2%80%99s%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2011%3A50%20am%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20the%20Dimapur%20airport%20by%20road%20and%20flew%20back%20to%20Guwahati%20at%2012%3A10%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20arrival%20at%20the%20Guwahati%20airport%20at%201%20pm%2C%20he%20travelled%20by%20road%20to%20his%20official%20residence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarma%E2%80%99s%20detailed%20itinerary%20didn%E2%80%99t%20mention%20any%20official%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Since%20the%20CMO%20said%20such%20%E2%80%98coincidences%E2%80%99%20(of%20official%20work%20and%20social%20engagements)%20were%20%E2%80%9Cfar%20and%20few%E2%80%9D%20from%20May%202021%2C%20when%20Sarma%20became%20Assam%20chief%20minister%2C%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20if%20his%20office%20meant%20to%20say%20that%20while%20those%20%E2%80%98coincidences%E2%80%99%20may%20have%20come%20down%20in%20Sarma%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20as%20compared%20to%20that%20of%20his%20predecessor%2C%20Sarbananda%20Sonowal%2C%20they%20do%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20noteworthy%20that%20while%20the%20Sarma%20government%20had%20claimed%20in%20the%20assembly%20last%20September%20that%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs%2034%2C13%2C42%2C303%20was%20spent%20from%20public%20funds%20to%20charter%20flights%20for%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20top%20dignitaries%2C%20including%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202022-23%2C%20the%20RTI%20replies%20received%20from%20the%20administration%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20CrossCurrent%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20however%2C%20showed%20only%20Rs%2019%2C74%2C62%2C657%20for%20that%20financial%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20discrepancy%20of%20Rs%2014%2C38%2C79%2C644%20between%20the%20two%20numbers.%20If%20the%20entire%20information%20is%20made%20public%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20more%20use%20of%20funds%20by%20the%20state%20government%20to%20charter%20special%20flights%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20non-governmental%20work%20may%20be%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20partial%20replies%20received%20through%20the%20RTI%20were%20denied%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20CrossCurrent%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20nearly%20a%20year%3B%20ultimately%2C%20incomplete%20replies%20were%20shared%20after%20the%20state%20information%20commission%20instructed%20the%20government%20to%20do%20so%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20news%20report%20has%20been%20published%20based%20on%20the%20RTI%20replies%20of%20the%20Sarma%20government.%20In%20the%20report%2C%20any%20official%20engagements%20that%20the%20chief%20minister%20took%20part%20in%20on%20dates%20mentioned%20in%20the%20RTI%20replies%2C%20along%20with%20the%20details%20of%20his%20engaging%20in%20party%20work%20or%20attending%20weddings%2C%20have%20been%20mentioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20report%20has%20also%20relied%20on%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20own%20social%20media%20handles%20to%20verify%20facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RTI%20replies%20of%20the%20Assam%20government%20can%20be%20perused%20here%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210756%2FGOSAIGAON-and-TAMULPUR-724x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22724%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210756%2FGOSAIGAON-and-TAMULPUR-724x1024.jpg%20724w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210756%2FGOSAIGAON-and-TAMULPUR-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210756%2FGOSAIGAON-and-TAMULPUR.jpg%20849w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695584%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%20%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210809%2FMCD-ELECTION-724x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22724%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210809%2FMCD-ELECTION-724x1024.jpg%20724w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03210809%2FMCD-ELECTION-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F202