inancial%20situation%20was%20unstable.%20My%20father%20used%20to%20repair%20bicycles%20while%20my%20mother%20travelled%20from%20one%20village%20to%20another%20selling%20bangles%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20jewellery.%20After%20taking%20my%20Class%2012%20exams%2C%20I%20went%20to%20Kerala%20for%20a%20year%20where%20I%20lived%20and%20studied%20at%20a%20Christian%20theological%20training%20institute%20in%20Thiruvalla%2C%20Kerala.%20The%20only%20requirement%20to%20study%20there%20was%20a%20matriculation%20certificate.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20his%20parents%20are%20unemployed%20but%20his%20elder%20brother%20runs%20a%20local%20Jan%20Seva%20Kendra%20(common%20services%20centre).%20These%20centres%20assist%20residents%20access%20essential%20services%20online%20such%20as%20Aadahaar%20and%20PAN%20card%20services%2C%20payment%20of%20household%20bills%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20was%20a%20two-year%20course%2C%20he%20only%20studied%20there%20for%20a%20year%20because%20of%20the%20national%20lockdown%20imposed%20following%20COVID-19.%20It%20was%20at%20this%20institute%20where%20he%20started%20learning%20English.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20weren%E2%80%99t%20allowed%20regular%20access%20to%20our%20mobile%20phones.%20Every%20Saturday%2C%20they%20would%20allow%20us%20to%20use%20our%20phones%20for%20three%20hours.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20a%20smartphone.%20I%20had%20a%20Jio%20phone%20with%20basic%20features.%20During%20one%20such%20session%2C%20I%20saw%20a%20video%20%5Bon%20YouTube%5D%20where%20I%20found%20someone%20teaching%20how%20to%20connect%20words%20and%20shorten%20them%20in%20spoken%20English%20conversation.%20That%20captivated%20me%20and%20I%20was%20interested%20to%20learn%20that%20kind%20of%20English%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20Dhiraj%20left%20Kerala%2C%20he%20began%20learning%20the%20%5BAmerican%5D%20accent%20that%20he%20currently%20employs%20in%20h